description: The create key operation can be used to create any key type in Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a new version of the key. It requires the keys/create permission.

tags.description: Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.

managed.description: True if the key's lifetime is managed by key vault. If this is a key backing a certificate, then managed will be true.

key_name.description: The name for the new key. The system will generate the version name for the new key.

parameters.description: The parameters to create a key.
